    • Method Detail

      • of

        public static <T> LuaObjectValue<T> of(T object)
        Returns a LuaObjectValue holding the provided object.

        If the given object is already held by an existing object value, the existing instance is returned. Otherwise, a new one is generated, registered and returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the Java type held by the object value
        Parameters:
        object - the Object for the value to hold
        Returns:
        the LuaObjectValue holding the provided object

      • orNil

        public static org.luaj.vm2.LuaValue orNil(java.lang.Object obj)
        Returns the LuaObjectValue representation of a Java object, or nil if it could not be created.

        Used for anything wanting to ensure null object values don't cause an exception.

        Parameters:
        obj - the object to wrap
        Returns:
        a LuaObjectValue, or nil
